        <abstract> 
<p>Reports long preparation of work on how species and varieties differ. Agreement with Wallace’s conclusions as reported in <hi rend="italic">Annals and Magazine of Natural History</hi> and in his letter to CD of 10 0ct [1856]. On distinction between domestic varieties and those in "a state of nature".</p> 
            <p>On mating of jaguars and leopards, the breeding of poultry, pigeons, etc.</p>
            <p>Requests help for his experimenting on means of distribution of organic beings on oceanic islands.</p>
        </abstract>
